message.content: A 65-year-old Caucasian male with a history of hypertension and hyperlipidemia presents with bone pain, fatigue, and recurrent infections. Workup reveals anemia, hypercalcemia, and monoclonal gammopathy, consistent with a diagnosis of multiple myeloma.
A 67-year-old Caucasian male with a history of hypertension presents with bone pain, fatigue, and recurrent infections, ultimately diagnosed with multiple myeloma.

A 65-year-old African American male with a history of chronic renal insufficiency presents with bone pain, fatigue, and recurrent infections. Workup reveals anemia, renal dysfunction, hypercalcemia, and monoclonal gammopathy. Diagnosis of multiple myeloma is made.

A 65-year-old Caucasian male with a history of hypertension presents with bone pain, fatigue, and recurrent infections, and is found to have anemia, hypercalcemia, and a monoclonal gammopathy on laboratory workup, consistent with a diagnosis of multiple myeloma.
